ce:section.ce:para:
Carbon nanodots were synthesized by hydrothermal method (Fig. 1
                        ). This procedure includes preparation of DSS aqueous solution, placing the solution into a special teflon cup and putting it to a stainless-steel autoclave. An autoclave is heated at constant temperature for 3 h at 220 °C. After cooling we centrifuged the obtained product and collected the supernatant solution containing CNDs. CNDs were obtained by the hydrothermal method from natural polymer, under these condition one can expect that the product might contain a mixture of luminescent carbon nanoparticles with different PL properties (Fig. 2
                        ). This is confirmed by initial PL data (Fig. 2a and b, 3D-PL spectra presented in supporting materials, Fig. S1a, b) which demonstrate excitation-dependent emission typically observed in CNDs.
